{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"> bringing its mathematical methods into parity with Matrix4\r\n\r\nActually, we made a conscious decision not to do that...\r\n\r\nOf course, we can revisit that decision.\r\n\r\nThe `Matrix3` methods include those methods required for the library to function. You are adding five new methods. There are many others you could add, including other `Matrix4` methods.\r\n\r\nWhat is your use case for these particular methods, and why should we include these methods and not others?","created_at":"2017-03-29T00:00:34.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11080#issuecomment-289941216","id":289941216,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11080","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI4OTk0MTIxNg==","updated_at":"2017-03-29T00:00:34.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/289941216","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Actually, `Matrix4.multiplyToArray()` has been removed in `dev`: https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/commit\/d8f7ccf26f8a9a530fd6c1e2646ff0e11a90f869\r\n\r\nYou can just do `multiplyMatrices( a, b ).toArray( r )`.","created_at":"2017-03-29T01:28:22.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11080#issuecomment-289954557","id":289954557,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11080","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI4OTk1NDU1Nw==","updated_at":"2017-03-29T01:29:48.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/289954557","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Both the use case for adding those methods and rationale for limiting it to them forms the bulk of my initial comment. I'm not proposing the addition of any methods to `Matrix4` - I'm proposing what subset of its functionality would be both intuitive and useful if present analogously in `Matrix3`. I realize there are as many opinions on what to include in a linear algebra class as there are linear algebra libraries, but I'd argue multiplication is not a controversial one.\r\n\r\nMy latest, specific use case that motivated this PR is to fit arbitrarily sized, user-submitted images to a prescribed width and height, and then scaling to NPOT for use as a texture. This is implemented as a product of up to three 3x3 affine matrices expressing 2D transforms: `npotScale \u2022 coverFit \u2022 arbitrary`. `coverFit` is computed and applied after examining `arbitrary`, which scales the image up to fill the target rectangle - but only if necessary. NPOT scaling is also done here to obviate three's handling of it at a predictable point in the application code. But even if I left that to three's autoscaling, I'm still multiplying at least two `Matrix3`s. A quick non-rigorous assessment of my options are:\r\n- pushing it down to a GLSL `*` of two `mat3`s, and applying it to the uvs\r\n- importing a separate library and doing all 3x3 matrix operations with that\r\n- writing a standalone function\r\n- monkeypatching `Matrix3`\r\n- the actual approach I went with, creating equivalent `Matrix4`s which apply no transform in the Z axis, then transferring back to a `Matrix3`.\r\n\r\nAll of these feel like coding around an interface wart - especially for such a fundamental operation, especially as a method present in matrices of one size and not another.","created_at":"2017-03-29T01:42:06.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11080#issuecomment-289956524","id":289956524,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11080","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI4OTk1NjUyNA==","updated_at":"2017-03-29T01:55:29.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/289956524","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1080102?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/yellcorp","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwODAxMDI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"yellcorp","type":"User","id":1080102,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"I included `multiplyToArray` for parity alone, so I won't defend its addition if the 4 equivalent is gone.","created_at":"2017-03-29T01:43:58.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11080#issuecomment-289956778","id":289956778,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11080","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI4OTk1Njc3OA==","updated_at":"2017-03-29T01:43:58.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/289956778","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1080102?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/yellcorp","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwODAxMDI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"yellcorp","type":"User","id":1080102,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"> I'd argue multiplication is not a controversial one.\r\n\r\nNeither are addition and subtraction. \r\n\r\nWhat is the argument for not adding those methods, too?\r\n\r\n. . .\r\n\r\nThis is not a math library. We have omitted many `Matrix3` methods, and we have no `Matrix2` class at all.\r\n\r\nPerhaps we could add convenience methods to `examples\/js\/math`?\r\n\r\nOr you could just add the required methods to your project.\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2017-03-29T03:00:53.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11080#issuecomment-289967694","id":289967694,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11080","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI4OTk2NzY5NA==","updated_at":"2017-03-29T03:00:53.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/289967694","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\