4`), and why it's preferable to the alternatives (interface consistency, and the read- and writability of application code that results). I don't think any of the extrapolations you mention are comparable. I'd say that addition and subtraction *are* more controversial due to their lesser relevance to geometric transformations, which supports the assertion it's not math library and these new methods don't detract from its focus.","created_at":"2017-03-29T22:34:48.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11080#issuecomment-290247112","id":290247112,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11080","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI5MDI0NzExMg==","updated_at":"2017-03-29T22:34:48.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/290247112","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1080102?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/yellcorp","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwODAxMDI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"yellcorp","type":"User","id":1080102,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yellcorp\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"I think in this case it's ok. Those methods are pretty common.","created_at":"2017-03-29T23:22:00.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\